data.enText: food/drink
to make food, drink, etc. go down your throat into your stomach

data.chText: 什么食物都要先嚼碎再吞咽。
data.enText: Always chew food well before swallowing it.
The pills should be swallowed whole.

data.chText: 当时我嗓子疼，咽东西就疼。
data.enText: I had a sore throat and it hurt to swallow.
move throat muscles
to move the muscles of your throat as if you were swallowing sth, especially because you are nervous

data.chText: 她硬下心把坏消息告诉了他。
data.enText: She swallowed hard and told him the bad news.
completely cover
to take sb/sth in or completely cover it so that they cannot be seen or no longer exist separately

data.chText: 我看着她沿公路越走越远，直至消失在黑暗中。
data.enText: I watched her walk down the road until she was swallowed by the darkness.

data.chText: 大片大片的乡村地区被城镇吞噬。
data.enText: Large areas of countryside have been swallowed up by towns.
use up money
to use up sth completely, especially an amount of money

data.chText: 我的工资大多支付房租和各种日常费用了。
data.enText: Most of my salary gets swallowed (up) by the rent and bills.
believe
to accept that sth is true; to believe sth

data.chText: 我觉得她的理由很难让人相信。
data.enText: I found her excuse very hard to swallow .

data.chText: 他对她讲了一堆假话，可她全都信以为真。
data.enText: He told her a pack of lies, but she swallowed it whole .
feelings
to hide your feelings
to swallow your doubts

data.chText: 你得放下架子，去求人家给你恢复原职。
data.enText: You're going to have to swallow your pride and ask for your job back.
accept insults
to accept insults, criticisms, etc. without complaining or protesting

data.chText: 让我吃惊的是他就坐在那儿默默地任凭他们评论。
data.enText: I was surprised that he just sat there and swallowed all their remarks.
a bitter pill (for sb) (to swallow)

data.chText: 严酷的现实；（难以咽下的）苦果
data.enText: a fact or an event that is unpleasant and difficult to accept
bird
a small bird with long pointed wings and a tail with two points, that spends the winter in Africa but flies to northern countries for the summer
of food/drink

data.chText: 咽；吞；一次吞咽的量；一口
data.enText: an act of swallowing; an amount of food or drink that is swallowed at one time
one swallow doesn't make a summer

data.chText: 别略有好事就以为佳时已到；好事可能纯属偶然；一燕不成夏（不能单凭微小的迹象而下定论）
data.enText: you must not take too seriously a small sign that sth is happening or will happen in the future, because the situation could change
a bitter pill (for sb) (to swallow)

data.chText: 严酷的现实；（难以咽下的）苦果
data.enText: a fact or an event that is unpleasant and difficult to accept
one swallow doesn't make a summer

data.chText: 别略有好事就以为佳时已到；好事可能纯属偶然；一燕不成夏（不能单凭微小的迹象而下定论）
data.enText: you must not take too seriously a small sign that sth is happening or will happen in the future, because the situation could change

example: one swallow of the liquid was enough
he took a drink of his beer and smacked his lips

tr: small long-winged songbird noted for swift graceful flight and the regularity of its migrations
a small amount of liquid food
believe or accept without questioning or challenge
example: Am I supposed to swallow that story?
I shall have to accept these unpleasant working conditions
She has learned to live with her husband's little idiosyncrasies
I swallowed my anger and kept quiet

tr: take back what one has said

example: She swallowed the last words of her speech
The Nazis swallowed the Baltic countries

tr: pass through the esophagus as part of eating or drinking
example: Swallow the raw fish--it won't kill you!

tr: enclose or envelop completely, as if by swallowing
example: The huge waves swallowed the small boat and it sank shortly thereafter

value.def: If you swallow something, you cause it to go from your mouth down into your stomach.

example.ex: You are asked to swallow a capsule containing vitamin B...
example.tran: 你要服一粒维生素 B 胶囊。

example.ex: Polly took a bite of the apple, chewed and swallowed.
example.tran: 波利咬了一口苹果，嚼了嚼咽了下去。

example.ex: Jan lifted her glass and took a quick swallow.
example.tran: 简拿起玻璃杯猛地喝了一口。

value.def: If you swallow, you make a movement in your throat as if you are swallowing something, often because you are nervous or frightened.

example.ex: Nancy swallowed hard and shook her head.
example.tran: 南希用力咽了口口水，摇了摇头。

value.tran: (常因为紧张或恐惧而)做吞咽动作，咽口水

value.def: If someone swallows a story or a statement, they believe it completely.

example.ex: It was vital that he swallowed the story about Juanita being in that motel room that night.
example.tran: 关键是他对朱厄妮塔那晚住在那个汽车旅馆房间里一事毫不怀疑。

example.ex: I too found this story a little hard to swallow.
example.tran: 我也觉得这件事有点难以置信。

value.def: If you swallow your feelings, you do not express them, although you want to very much.

example.ex: Gordon has swallowed the anger he felt...
example.tran: 戈登忍住了内心的愤怒。

example.ex: He flashed me a quick grin but rapidly swallowed it when he saw my expression.
example.tran: 他先是冲我咧嘴一笑，不过看到我的表情后又赶紧收起笑脸。

value.def: A swallow is a kind of small bird with pointed wings and a forked tail.
